menopause, Helen.

05:53.813 --> 05:56.550
That's why your period is late.

05:58.847 --> 06:00.917
You know, things can happen.

06:01.105 --> 06:03.105
It's not impossible.

06:03.498 --> 06:06.178
Janet Jackson was older than me.

06:08.157 --> 06:10.519
Don't you think I'm too young
to be in menopause?

06:11.795 --> 06:13.910
Don't you think
I'm too young to die?

06:18.063 --> 06:19.105
Vik, wait.

06:19.189 --> 06:20.628
Kids, let's go!

06:23.490 --> 06:25.345
I'll make sure
he takes them, Mom.

06:25.810 --> 06:26.857
Thanks, baby.

06:26.934 --> 06:28.439
Bye.

07:02.392 --> 07:03.480
Helen.

07:03.563 --> 07:04.737
Oh, my God,
you scared me.

07:04.814 --> 07:06.361
Hi.

07:08.432 --> 07:09.672
You want some?

07:10.813 --> 07:13.429
Yeah. Sure.

07:17.563 --> 07:19.778
I know you hate California.

07:19.855 --> 07:22.348
You have to admit,
we have better weed.

07:22.537 --> 07:24.315
When did I say
I hated California?

07:24.392 --> 07:25.755
I can just tell.

07:25.832 --> 07:28.653
You're one of those
East Coast snobs

07:28.730 --> 07:31.934
who just loves to act
like you're in exile out here.

07:34.397 --> 07:37.363
Oh, no. Where is that
cookbook your mother wrote?

07:37.725 --> 07:38.898
It's in there.

07:38.975 --> 07:40.663
- Yeah, but which one?
- See, the thing that you

07:40.730 --> 07:42.450
transplants don't understand

07:42.527 --> 07:46.019
is that California is actually
the cradle of civilization.

07:46.096 --> 07:48.809
Uh, actually, I think that's
somewhere in the Middle East.

07:49.022 --> 07:52.345
Yeah, if you're talking
about patriarchal society.

07:52.779 --> 07:55.257
I'm talking about
matriarchal society.

07:55.334 --> 07:57.208
And you think that started here?

07:57.285 --> 07:58.927
Not right here.

07:59.004 --> 08:01.440
About 150 miles east,
in Joshua Tree.

08:01.517 --> 08:02.936
Sierra?

08:03.709 --> 08:06.840
You know nothing you're saying
is true, right?

08:09.605 --> 08:10.940
Such a cynic.

08:13.897 --> 08:15.105
I win.

08:15.303 --> 08:16.355
Oh, wait.

08:16.615 --> 08:17.937
No, I don't.

08:18.014 --> 08:19.271
You know, I wouldn't
have figured you

08:19.338 --> 08:20.957
for a solitaire type of girl.

08:21.108 --> 08:23.286
My mom taught me
when I was a kid

08:23.363 --> 08:26.394
so that I could keep myself
entertained when she was on set.

08:26.706 --> 08:29.446
I didn't really have
many friends my own age.

08:29.806 --> 08:31.629
That's why I'm such an old soul.

08:33.402 --> 08:35.605
No, you're not an old anything.

08:35.826 --> 08:39.136
Helen, I'm gonna
be 30 next year.

08:39.225 --> 08:40.304
Wow.

08:40.381 --> 08:42.488
No, you don't understand.

08:42.607 --> 08:46.397
Thirty is almost, like,
50 in actor years.

08:46.474 --> 08:49.302
Well, I'm almost, like,
50 in people years.

08:49.379 --> 08:51.394
Yeah, but you're still
really fuckable.

08:51.537 --> 08:53.154
I'm never gonna be
that fuckable

08:53.231 --> 08:54.970
when I'm your age.

08:55.412 --> 08:56.970
What time is it?

08:57.154 --> 08:58.403
I don't know.

08:58.480 --> 09:00.023
Alexa, what time is it?

09:00.100 --> 09:02.296
The time is 11:04 a.m.

09:02.373 --> 09:04.504
