you can tell

11:35.012 --> 11:36.481
if he's serious
about commitment.

11:36.558 --> 11:38.611
That's what my mom
always said.

11:38.688 --> 11:39.950
You're gonna think
I'm full of it,

11:40.017 --> 11:42.429
but I wish I had your life.

11:43.131 --> 11:44.505
Oh.

11:44.855 --> 11:46.278
No, you don't.

11:46.355 --> 11:47.945
No, I'm serious.

11:48.022 --> 11:50.488
I would so much rather be you.

11:50.936 --> 11:52.636
I mean,
look at my life.

11:52.713 --> 11:54.055
Yeah?

11:54.132 --> 11:57.138
Literally, the only
currency that I have

11:57.215 --> 11:59.546
is my youth

11:59.623 --> 12:02.637
or my sex or whatever.

12:03.409 --> 12:05.742
But you...

12:06.561 --> 12:08.023
you, like, have it all.

12:08.100 --> 12:10.684
No, you're...

12:12.576 --> 12:15.507
You're, like,
this smart, beautiful,

12:15.584 --> 12:16.812
sophisticated woman.

12:16.889 --> 12:18.224
You've made all
the right choices.

12:18.301 --> 12:20.005
You have...

12:20.082 --> 12:21.279
I mean,
you don't have men

12:21.356 --> 12:23.364
chewing you up
and spitting you out.

12:23.441 --> 12:26.512
You have a family
and Vik and...

12:26.803 --> 12:29.570
I mean, you have a whole world
that needs you.

12:29.647 --> 12:32.019
Like, literally
couldn't live without you.

12:33.030 --> 12:34.936
How do I get that?

12:38.364 --> 12:41.563
♪ To build it back again ♪

12:43.980 --> 12:47.621
♪ Build the peaceable kingdom ♪

12:50.189 --> 12:51.272
See?

12:51.355 --> 12:53.012
♪ Back again ♪

12:53.162 --> 12:54.605
Told you.

12:54.803 --> 12:56.036
Pretty great, right?

12:56.113 --> 12:58.606
♪ Build it back again ♪

12:58.683 --> 13:00.314
Come on.

13:02.932 --> 13:05.990
We're gonna miss the
Blessing of the Eagle Feather.

13:11.897 --> 13:16.736
I want you all to take
a big, deep breath.

13:16.813 --> 13:21.694
We've made it to the new moon
in tropical Libra.

13:21.771 --> 13:23.690
We call upon this new moon,
our cosmic mother...

13:23.767 --> 13:24.934
That's Gaelle?

13:25.011 --> 13:26.065
Yeah. Isn't she
wonderful?

13:26.142 --> 13:27.486
You said she was a guru.

13:27.563 --> 13:29.481
- She is.
- Join us...

13:29.558 --> 13:30.604
She's a teenager.

13:30.681 --> 13:31.940
Well, she was
an Incan princess

13:32.017 --> 13:33.528
in a past life.

13:33.605 --> 13:35.565
Help us uncover
our first selves...

13:35.642 --> 13:39.146
I don't care if you don't
believe me. It's true.

13:39.476 --> 13:41.446
We call upon fire...

13:41.523 --> 13:43.565
Is she even allowed
to wear that thing?

13:43.642 --> 13:45.237
- What do you mean?
- I mean,

13:45.314 --> 13:46.876
it's kind of
politically incorrect.

13:46.953 --> 13:48.217
- Shh.
- I mean, how many birds

13:48.294 --> 13:50.107
- had to die to make...
- Okay, Helen. Shh.

13:50.184 --> 13:54.149
Let its great power
transmute our negative,

13:54.226 --> 13:56.178
lower energies.

13:56.461 --> 13:57.731
And help us

13:57.808 --> 13:59.952
move forward into positivity

14:00.029 --> 14:01.351
and light.

14:04.646 --> 14:07.499
For people whose chakras
are particularly blocked,

14:07.576 --> 14:09.587
the sage is very powerful.

14:09.664 --> 14:11.499
I'm allergic to sage.

14:11.576 --> 14:13.373
It's...

14:13.450 --> 14:15.778
It's Helen, right?

14:15.855 --> 14:17.565
- Mm-hmm.
- You're lucky the universe

14:17.642 --> 14:20.304
chose to partner you
with Sierra here.

14:20.687 --> 14:22.217
I've rarely met a sister

14:22.294 --> 14:24.595
whose sacral chakra
is more aligned.

14:52.521 --> 14:54.023
Get a yurt!

15:01.865 --> 15:04.105
Thank you for holding space.

15:04.230 --> 15:08.012
Thank you for receiving light.

15:21.855 --> 15:23.820
Oh, my God, I hate

15:23.897 --> 15:26.716
having to wear clothes
all the time. Don't you?

15:28.147 --> 15:30.606
That's what I love
about being out here.

15:30.683 --> 15:32.315
There's not
a man in sight.

15:32.392 --> 15:35.224
It's so liberating.

15:35.570 --> 15:37.023
Uh...

15:37.100 --> 15:38.690
So, what's the, um...

15:38.767 --> 15:40.493
What's on the, uh...

15:40.570 --> 15:42.285
What are we doing tonight?

15:42.362 --> 15:44.655
Well, I don't know exactly.

15:44.732 --> 15:47.647
Um, with Gaelle,
anything could happen,

15:47.724 --> 15:50.486
but we usually have a banquet,

15:50.563 --> 15:52.458
and then we do the moon circle.

15:52.539 --> 15:53.539
Cool.

15:54.105 --> 15:56.810
Ooh. This...

15:57.265 --> 16:00.421
is for you to wear to dinner.

16:00.498 --> 16:02.966
Oh, uh, do I have to?

16:03.523 --> 16:05.634
Well, no, you don't have to,

16:05.711 --> 16:07.813
but I don't know
how you expect to have

16:07.890 --> 16:09.315
a transformative experience

16:09.392 --> 16:11.512
if you don't at least try
to participate.

16:14.203 --> 16:15.794
What is that?

16:15.875 --> 16:17.335
