Of course.

37:45.688 --> 37:47.710
You better not be
heading for the Switch.

37:47.787 --> 37:48.986
It's my day!

37:49.063 --> 37:51.231
Helen!
What did you do with my razor?

37:51.308 --> 37:52.409
Hey, knock it off.

37:52.476 --> 37:53.564
What?

37:53.641 --> 37:55.939
Razor!
It doesn't have a blade.

37:56.016 --> 37:58.640
Well, I threw it away.
It was dull. Oh, hi.

37:58.717 --> 38:01.205
It was only dull because
you shaved your legs with it!

38:01.282 --> 38:04.429
There's more of them
in the top, right-hand drawer.

38:04.902 --> 38:06.918
How was the lesson?

38:06.995 --> 38:09.118
- Can I talk to you?
- Yeah, sure.

38:09.228 --> 38:11.547
You'd lose your mind
if I went into your room!

38:11.624 --> 38:13.116
I didn't go
into your room!

38:13.193 --> 38:15.897
I swear to God,
if you guys don't stop...

38:15.974 --> 38:17.369
You and Vik need
to work with me.

38:17.446 --> 38:19.360
- Work with you?
- I am trying

38:19.488 --> 38:20.813
so hard.

38:21.167 --> 38:22.320
I've upended my life

38:22.397 --> 38:24.158
to follow you here
for Vik's work,

38:24.235 --> 38:25.736
- to be near my kids.
- Yeah, me too.

38:25.813 --> 38:27.117
And you guys
won't meet me halfway.

38:27.184 --> 38:29.056
I don't... What?

38:29.147 --> 38:30.971
This is supposed to be
a partnership, Helen.

38:31.048 --> 38:33.057
We are co-parenting,
and right now,

38:33.134 --> 38:35.134
I am the only one
extending myself.

38:35.683 --> 38:38.391
You won't encourage
the kids to call back.

38:38.874 --> 38:40.905
You roll over my visitation.

38:40.982 --> 38:44.066
Vik is incredibly competitive
with the kids.

38:44.143 --> 38:46.836
I mean, for fuck's sake,
Helen, they are my children.

38:46.972 --> 38:48.354
Not his.

38:48.980 --> 38:51.485
You just need to tell him
to back the fuck up.

38:51.615 --> 38:53.104
He's dying.

38:56.688 --> 38:58.531
Vik has cancer,

38:59.439 --> 39:03.095
and he's going
to die soon, so...

39:05.065 --> 39:06.274
maybe you'll forgive us

39:06.351 --> 39:08.262
if we aren't
at our best right now.

39:11.198 --> 39:12.774
What kind of cancer?

39:12.851 --> 39:14.977
Does it matter?

39:16.204 --> 39:17.611
The kids know?

39:21.767 --> 39:23.321
Oh, God.

39:24.939 --> 39:26.617
You should have told me.

39:27.189 --> 39:28.969
Why would I
have told you?

39:29.189 --> 39:30.580
Because we're friends.

39:30.657 --> 39:32.345
No, we're not.

39:36.096 --> 39:37.803
Jesus, Helen, I...

39:38.029 --> 39:39.520
I'm so sorry.

39:41.213 --> 39:42.671
Look, I-if there's
anything you need,

39:42.748 --> 39:43.748
anything I can do...

39:43.821 --> 39:45.184
I-I can take the kids.

39:45.261 --> 39:47.126
You and Vik
can have some time.

39:48.063 --> 39:50.220
Oh, God, Helen, I...

39:52.688 --> 39:53.822
Sorry. I can also...

39:53.899 --> 39:56.039
I can just give
you guys some space.

39:56.182 --> 39:57.678
That would be great.

39:59.558 --> 40:00.900
Sure.

40:02.143 --> 40:03.338
Thank you.

40:22.521 --> 40:23.648
Hey.

40:23.725 --> 40:25.304
What the fuck?

40:25.825 --> 40:28.124
Sorry. Your-your door was open.

40:28.201 --> 40:30.155
Did I scare you?

40:31.755 --> 40:33.095
No.

40:34.138 --> 40:35.313
It's the hoodie, right?

40:35.390 --> 40:36.940
The hoodie makes me
seem threatening.

40:37.017 --> 40:38.017
Better?

40:38.239 --> 40:39.745
That's not funny.

40:39.919 --> 40:41.095
Yeah, it is.

40:49.386 --> 40:51.886
Well, now that you've
made yourself at home...

40:52.519 --> 40:54.337
want to tell me why you're here?

40:55.189 --> 40:57.178
How do you even
know where I live?

40:57.284 --> 40:59.368
Read through my mom's
personnel files.

40:59.667 --> 41:01.431
I've seen all your pay stubs.

41:03.439 --> 41:06.220
Well, then you should have known
not to eat all my prosciutto.

41:06.511 --> 41:09.040
I'm playing.
I-I White-Paged you, actually.

41:09.628 --> 41:11.032
It's that easy, huh?

41:11.128 --> 41:12.387
That's disturbing.

41:12.464 --> 41:14.212
Yeah, I think you
can get it blocked.

41:18.646 --> 41:20.556
I need your thoughts.

41:22.066 --> 41:23.652
Okay. What about?

41:23.729 --> 41:25.798
On whether or not
I should join the Marines.

41:25.875 --> 41:27.019
What?

41:27.964 --> 41:29.101
What about college?

41:29.178 --> 41:31.582
I need to be my own man,
Mr. Solloway.

41:31.659 --> 41:32.934
I-I can't keep
letting my parents

41:33.001 --> 41:34.440
push me around like this.

41:34.517 --> 41:35.899
It's not right.

41:37.698 --> 41:38.932
Look, I know you and my mom

41:39.009 --> 41:41.001
have something
going on right now.

41:42.116 --> 41:43.853
She can be a real bully.

41:44.120 --> 41:45.198
You should know that.

41:45.275 --> 41:47.282
Yeah, I do know that, Anton.

41:49.230 --> 41:52.354
I also know that she loves you
like a crazy person,

41:52.431 --> 41:54.648
and right now she's having
a hard time letting you go.

41:54.725 --> 41:56.190
And that's normal.
That's not her.

41:56.267 --> 41:58.211
That's just what happens
when the time comes

41:58.288 --> 42:00.126
for kids to
flee the nest.

42:00.521 --> 42:03.178
You'd really rather go to war
than go to college?

42:03.292 --> 42:06.080
Well, they said the chances
of me seeing combat are slim.

42:06.157 --> 42:07.325
Yeah, they're lying.

42:07.402 --> 42:08.482
This country is pretty much

42:08.558 --> 42:11.540
at war somewhere
all the time.

42:11.813 --> 42:14.678
Well, any way I go,

42:14.847 --> 42:17.262
one of them is going
to be disappointed.

42:20.188 --> 42:22.762
Look, you came here.
You want my advice, right?

42:25.646 --> 42:27.678
I really think
you need to see Princeton.

42:27.870 --> 42:29.345
Just see it. Just...

42:29.441 --> 42:31.149
spend some time there.

42:31.338 --> 42:33.565
You have this idea in your head
that it's a terrible place.

42:33.632 --> 42:35.669
Maybe it is,
but maybe you'd like it.

42:35.761 --> 42:37.242
Well, how am I supposed
to pull that off?

42:37.309 --> 42:38.787
It's all the way
across the country.

42:38.941 --> 42:40.112
Your mom will take you there.

42:40.189 --> 42:41.301
No, she won't.

42:41.378 --> 42:43.307
- How do you know?
- I just do.

42:43.384 --> 42:44.946
Have you asked her?

42:48.165 --> 42:49.907
How did you get here?
You drive?

42:49.984 --> 42:51.924
No, I Ubered.
I never get to drive.

42:52.001 --> 42:53.571
I don't have a fucking car.

42:53.761 --> 42:55.028
Okay. Let's go.

42:55.105 --> 42:56.065
Where are we going?

42:56.142 --> 42:57.315
To talk to your mom.

42:57.392 --> 42:58.848
No. I just got here.

42:58.925 --> 43:00.075
She'll kill me
if she finds out

43:00.142 --> 43:01.351
- I came to you.
- Come on.

43:01.428 --> 43:02.881
I'll let you drive.

43:03.313 --> 43:04.804
Down the PCH.

43:20.314 --> 43:23.899
Why can't you rebel
like a normal kid?

43:24.823 --> 43:27.470
Go to Europe for a year.
Date a white girl.

43:27.613 --> 43:29.239
You really want to fuck
with me and your dad?

43:29.306 --> 43:32.112
Do the Peace Corps in some
awful third-world place.

43:32.189 --> 43:34.190
Don't join the fucking Army.

43:34.267 --> 43:36.713
- Marines.
- Boy, I will kill you.

43:36.790 --> 43:38.982
Look, if I go to the Marines,
I won't be a victim.

43:39.059 --> 43:40.315
What are you
talking about?

43:40.392 --> 43:42.315
How is shooting
other brown people

43:42.392 --> 43:44.731
gonna give you agency?
Hear yourself.

43:44.808 --> 43:46.153
No, hear yourself.

43:46.230 --> 43:48.595
It is always about race
and agency with you.

43:48.777 --> 43:50.153
What nine-year-old has

43:50.230 --> 43:51.963
a Black Revolutionary-themed
birthday party?

43:52.040 --> 43:53.901
Fucking Marcus Garvey
on the chocolate cake?

43:53.978 --> 43:55.153
Malcolm X napkins?

43:55.230 --> 43:57.195
- Like, who does that?
- They make those?

43:57.272 --> 43:59.410
Yes. This is what I've had
to deal with my whole life.

43:59.487 --> 44:01.227
- To protect you.
- Look, if I have a target

44:01.304 --> 44:03.212
on my back,
why shouldn't I sign up?

44:03.552 --> 44:05.399
At least then
I'll have a gun.

44:07.103 --> 44:09.235
- What are you doing here?
- Your mother called.

44:09.472 --> 44:11.350
She didn't know where you went.

44:11.427 --> 44:13.752
You can't disappear without
telling her where you're going.

44:13.829 --> 44:15.354
You know that.
She worries.

44:15.431 --> 44:17.220
Why? I'm 19 years old.

44:17.298 --> 44:18.495
Tell him.

44:18.597 --> 44:19.605
Go on.

44:19.688 --> 44:20.982
You're such an adult.
Tell him.

44:21.059 --> 44:22.470
Tell him
what you did.

44:23.756 --> 44:25.773
I talked to a recruiter
about joining the Marines.

44:25.850 --> 44:26.973
You did what?

44:27.050 --> 44:28.481
Uh...

44:28.558 --> 44:29.762
Hi.

44:29.839 --> 44:31.940
Does this motherfucker
live here now?

44:32.017 --> 44:34.104
Look, I-I know
it's not my place...

44:34.181 --> 44:35.486
Oh, you're damn right.

44:35.563 --> 44:36.982
But your kid came to my house

44:37.059 --> 44:38.886
looking for help, so...

44:39.183 --> 44:41.231
I thought maybe we could all
just talk about it.

44:41.308 --> 44:43.088
Who the fuck does
your boyfriend think he is?

44:43.165 --> 44:44.356
He's not my boyfriend.

44:44.433 --> 44:45.922
Reason he wants
to join the Marines

44:45.999 --> 44:48.246
is because he can't
make a decision

44:48.323 --> 44:49.609
about this Princeton thing

44:49.686 --> 44:53.056
because he is terrified
of hurting one of you.

44:53.566 --> 44:55.237
So, what I suggested
was that

44:55.314 --> 44:57.274
somebody should just
take him there.

44:57.480 --> 44:59.399
Let him see the school,
see if he likes it,

44:59.476 --> 45:00.648
make his own decision.

45:00.725 --> 45:01.945
Sounds reasonable to me.

45:02.022 --> 45:03.229
If I go, it'd have to be

45:03.306 --> 45:04.736
- this week.
- Why?

45:04.813 --> 45:07.665
Because I scheduled
to take the GED next Monday.

45:08.402 --> 45:10.973
Anton... in order
to take the GED,

45:11.050 --> 45:12.776
you have to drop out
of high school.

45:12.853 --> 45:15.103
I can't join the Marines
without it.

45:15.253 --> 45:16.945
- Oh, no.
- You have school this week.

45:17.022 --> 45:19.153
Hell no. You're not joining
the fucking military.

45:19.230 --> 45:20.653
Look, I can miss
a couple classes.

45:20.730 --> 45:22.413
I already took these
fucking classes anyway.

45:22.480 --> 45:23.957
Boy, don't talk like that
to your mother.

45:24.024 --> 45:25.325
Why is it,
whenever you're mad at me,

45:25.392 --> 45:26.616
you act like
you're still her man?

45:26.683 --> 45:28.112
- You want to live?
- Oh, Jesus.

45:28.189 --> 45:29.798
Not another word.

45:29.938 --> 45:31.567
Look, Carl, my friend...

45:31.644 --> 45:33.653
Man, why are you
all up in my family?

45:33.730 --> 45:35.056
You don't have your own?

45:35.205 --> 45:36.447
Yeah, I do.

45:36.524 --> 45:38.579
Then what the fuck
you doing here?

45:39.589 --> 45:41.290
Anton, go to your room.

45:41.504 --> 45:42.954
Carl, go home.

45:43.031 --> 45:45.645
Let's... let's just
sleep on this, okay?

45:45.722 --> 45:47.242
We don't have to make
any decisions tonight.

45:47.309 --> 45:48.648
We don't have to do anything.

45:48.725 --> 45:50.694
- It's my decision.
- Okay.

45:50.771 --> 45:53.096
If you want
to go to the school,

45:53.173 --> 45:55.195
I'll take you
this week. I promise.

45:55.272 --> 45:56.846
Janelle, what about
the board meeting?

45:56.923 --> 45:58.075
This is more important.

45:58.152 --> 45:59.252
Janelle, hold up.

45:59.329 --> 46:00.596
We talked about
sending him

46:00.673 --> 46:03.121
to a state school...
Public education.

46:03.198 --> 46:04.176
We agreed on that

46:04.253 --> 46:05.155
when he was a baby.

46:05.232 --> 46:07.735
- Things have changed, Carl.
- No, you've changed.

46:07.812 --> 46:09.754
- Dad, what if I want to go?
- Anton, just be quiet.

46:09.821 --> 46:11.168
Just because you
couldn't make it there

46:11.235 --> 46:12.210
doesn't mean I can't.

46:12.287 --> 46:13.447
Carl!

46:13.524 --> 46:14.646
Hey.

46:16.646 --> 46:18.234
You gonna hit me?

46:18.579 --> 46:19.823
Hit me.

46:20.919 --> 46:22.545
Go ahead.

46:24.246 --> 46:25.371
Carl.

46:31.688 --> 46:33.945
So you a man now.

46:35.569 --> 46:37.559
Okay, be a man.

46:40.619 --> 46:42.469
Go see what it's like.

47:08.029 --> 47:09.895
Hi. It's Whitney.
Leave a message.

47:09.972 --> 47:11.986
Hey, Whit, it's Dad.

47:12.063 --> 47:13.736
Uh, it's super late
where you are.

47:13.813 --> 47:15.767
You're probably asleep,
but I just, uh...

47:15.844 --> 47:17.184
I was just calling to say hi.

47:17.261 --> 47:20.334
Mom keeps me informed
about most things, but, um...

47:20.922 --> 47:22.842
good to hear from you
once in a while.

47:22.980 --> 47:24.709
It's been a while.

47:25.414 --> 47:26.694
Okay. Love you.

47:26.771 --> 47:28.201
Call me if you can.

47:28.278 --> 47:30.236
If you feel like it. Bye.

47:57.774 --> 48:00.345
- Hey.
- Hey.

48:02.755 --> 48:04.179
Can I come in?

48:04.256 --> 48:05.563
Of course.

48:10.480 --> 48:11.605
It's nice.

48:11.688 --> 48:13.189
Thanks.

48:13.272 --> 48:14.731
You renting?

48:14.808 --> 48:16.147
Yeah.

48:16.230 --> 48:17.355
Thank God.

48:17.439 --> 48:19.444
How did you find me?

48:19.521 --> 48:22.611
Um, I made Anton
tell me where you live.

48:22.688 --> 48:24.357
What, and you drove
all the way up here

48:24.434 --> 48:25.773
in the middle
of the night?

48:25.850 --> 48:28.399
You didn't call
or text or...?

48:28.476 --> 48:29.903
Should I go?

48:29.980 --> 48:31.648
No, no, please, no.

48:31.725 --> 48:33.646
Sit down.

48:33.730 --> 48:36.773
Can I get you anything?
I... I've got whiskey.

48:36.850 --> 48:40.078
You can, but let me just
say something first.

48:41.353 --> 48:44.259
Thank you for what you did.

48:44.719 --> 48:46.070
I didn't do anything.

48:46.147 --> 48:47.494
No, you did.

48:47.571 --> 48:49.220
You stood up for my son.

48:49.680 --> 48:51.615
That was crazy earlier.

48:51.735 --> 48:54.224
Well, we've all been there.

48:56.480 --> 48:58.554
We've been, uh...

48:58.977 --> 49:01.056
divorced for so long,

49:01.133 --> 49:03.512
you'd think we'd be
over it by now,

49:03.633 --> 49:05.970
figured out a way
to forgive each other,

49:06.235 --> 49:08.053
find some peace.

49:08.453 --> 49:10.592
But somehow...

49:11.703 --> 49:13.967
They say time
heals all wounds,

49:14.044 --> 49:15.803
but sometimes it doesn't.

49:17.071 --> 49:18.278
No, it doesn't.

49:18.355 --> 49:20.429
It just makes things worse.

49:21.985 --> 49:24.201
Anyway, I just...

49:26.397 --> 49:28.898
Of course he should have
seen the damn school.

49:28.975 --> 49:30.761
I should have taken him.

49:32.855 --> 49:34.720
I'm gonna take him this week.

49:35.969 --> 49:37.709
What about the board meeting?

49:37.786 --> 49:39.329
What about it?

49:39.406 --> 49:41.595
If they fire me, they fire me.

49:44.149 --> 49:46.137
Look, what if I take him?

49:47.972 --> 49:49.305
You?

49:49.438 --> 49:50.687
I'm the neutral party.

49:50.764 --> 49:53.126
I can take him there,
introduce him to my friend.

49:53.203 --> 49:54.864
He can observe a class.

49:55.022 --> 49:57.429
Then we come back,
and he can make his decision.

49:58.156 --> 49:59.636
You'd do that?

49:59.922 --> 50:01.369
I'd be happy to do it.

50:01.446 --> 50:02.802
If it's okay with you.

50:02.879 --> 50:05.082
And Carl, of course.

50:05.438 --> 50:07.001
If it's a choice between this

50:07.078 --> 50:08.773
and the goddamn Marines,
who knows?

50:08.850 --> 50:10.365
Maybe he would.

50:10.972 --> 50:12.546
He should go.

50:19.439 --> 50:22.154
Why are you doing this, Noah?

50:23.399 --> 50:25.845
You really think my son
is that brilliant?

50:27.967 --> 50:29.818
Yeah, I do.

50:30.789 --> 50:32.686
But I'm not doing it for him.

50:47.897 --> 50:49.563
Mmm.

51:17.442 --> 51:18.632
Does it turn you on

51:18.709 --> 51:19.992
- that I'm your boss?
- Oh, Jesus.

51:20.059 --> 51:22.097
Janelle, shut the fuck up.

51:38.480 --> 51:40.959
Oh, my. Oh, my.

51:41.063 --> 51:43.274
Oh, my God.

51:45.147 --> 51:46.605
Oh, my.

51:56.314 --> 51:58.147
Oh, fuck.

52:08.938 --> 52:10.486
Excuse me.
Can you tell me

52:10.563 --> 52:12.444
what the connecting gate
to New York is?

52:12.521 --> 52:13.815
We don't have
that information.

52:13.892 --> 52:15.573
You'll have to check in
on the ground.

52:15.650 --> 52:17.270
Okay, thanks.

52:18.321 --> 52:19.778
Hey.

52:19.914 --> 52:21.653
Because we were
delayed taking off,

52:21.730 --> 52:23.530
we're gonna have to book it
when we hit the ground

52:23.597 --> 52:24.984
to make our
connection, okay?

52:25.061 --> 52:26.553
Should've got a direct flight.

52:27.480 --> 52:29.117
Yeah, well, your mother
booked this yesterday.

52:29.184 --> 52:31.220
We were lucky to get
any flight at all.

52:32.589 --> 52:34.204
Did you talk to your dad?

52:34.829 --> 52:36.610
He won't call me back.

52:42.272 --> 52:44.023
You're listening to my book?

52:44.100 --> 52:45.189
Yeah.

52:45.508 --> 52:47.345
It's pretty good, actually.

52:48.126 --> 52:49.492
Thanks.

52:53.868 --> 52:55.420
What?

52:55.497 --> 52:56.928
That's weird.

52:59.681 --> 53:00.888
Yo.

53:05.055 --> 53:06.717
Hi.

53:06.824 --> 53:09.685
Uh, we missed our connecting
flight to New York, so...

53:09.762 --> 53:10.891
Uh, no.

53:11.867 --> 53:13.153
"No"?

53:13.230 --> 53:16.115
No, we have no more flights
to New York today.

53:16.355 --> 53:18.204
What about the shuttle?

53:18.281 --> 53:20.158
They're all booked.

53:20.235 --> 53:22.494
We've had delays all day
because of the wind.

53:22.571 --> 53:23.546
What about standby?

53:23.623 --> 53:25.467
Good luck with standby.

53:25.571 --> 53:27.193
Come on, is there anything
you can do to help?

53:27.260 --> 53:30.959
Well, let me see
if I can switch you to...

53:31.036 --> 53:32.082
Ah.

53:32.625 --> 53:34.619
Tomorrow night, 8:23.

53:34.696 --> 53:36.232
No, we have to get
to New York tonight.

53:36.309 --> 53:38.012
Then rent a car.

53:45.730 --> 53:47.648
They're gonna
run out of cars.

53:53.332 --> 53:54.998
Cole?

53:58.303 --> 53:59.813
Wait.

54:01.214 --> 54:02.620
Wait. Cole, slow down.

